track_notes: Track from April 2014 by Terry G0VWP and submitted on his behalf.
track_title: Track from spot height 310 on OS 25K map

track_notes: There is a car park at the start of the trail. I was walking in the cold when the path was frozen so it was not too difficult. Looking at the number of bridges it could be quite boggy in warmer weather. The route is well way marked thanks to the friends of the the Pentlands. At the summit there is a wall and fence so a bit of shelter and an antenna fixing place. Walk time 2hr,
track_title: From Little Vantage Car Par on the A70
